                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 4001/2.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">British Chargé</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">British Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-01-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 17, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that I have been
                    instructed by His Majesty’s principal secretary of state for foreign affairs to
                    express the high appreciation of His Majesty’s Government at the prompt
                    assistance rendered by the United States Government in the dispatch of their
                    ships to Jamaica to afford aid to the stricken population of Kingston.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Esme Howard.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
